  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Afghanistan Community Health Programme</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The development of the ARCS Community health care provision through a national programme building on the learning and experiences in community health WASH and nutrition from the previous project undertaken in northern Afghanistan. It will focus specifically on rural and hard to reach areas where 76% of country s population live; including so-called white zones where no governmental healthcare facilities exist 1 where access to healthcare is extremely poor and where the reach of ARCS means that it can have the greatest impact. 1 Areas mapped by the MOPH where no Governmental facilities are present or able to work for security reasons. Current estimates suggest that these areas cover 35% of the country. Once Government control is lost health services are equally disrupted or ceased.</narrative>
  </description>
